<div id="review_208624820" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/208624820" />
    <a title="Therese" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6108634-therese"><img alt="Therese" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1564055680p2/6108634.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/208624820?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Therese" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Therese" href="/user/show/6108634-therese">Therese</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6108634-therese?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6108634-therese?shelf=literary-and-general-fiction">literary-and-general-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6108634-therese?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6108634-therese?shelf=top-favorites">top-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6108634-therese?shelf=page-turners">page-turners</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer208624820" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9605611712176433375">I read this ages ago, but was reminded of it again because with all the controversy over American Dirt, a lot of people have been talking about their favorite books by Mexican and Mexican-American authors. (I loved American Dirt, as you can see from <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3158151630?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1' rel='nofollow noopener'>my review</a>, but have found all the reading recommendations a positive byproduct of the sometimes-toxic controversy!) On that note, I wanted to give Rain of Gold a shout-out because I remember it being one of my top favorite books of all time, and it p</span>
  <span id="freeText9605611712176433375" style="display:none">I read this ages ago, but was reminded of it again because with all the controversy over American Dirt, a lot of people have been talking about their favorite books by Mexican and Mexican-American authors. (I loved American Dirt, as you can see from <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3158151630?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener">my review</a>, but have found all the reading recommendations a positive byproduct of the sometimes-toxic controversy!) On that note, I wanted to give Rain of Gold a shout-out because I remember it being one of my top favorite books of all time, and it probably was a way-back inspiration for me to eventually try my own hand at writing magical realist historical fiction. I think that was a much newer concept for fiction back when Villasenor did it, and Villasenor's beautiful writing and his philosophy of faith and hope, along with the unforgettable events he describes, all combined to blow my mind. I really need to go back and re-read it, because I remember the first time I read it I was still at a time in my life when I thought a lot about religion and the meaning of faith. Now that I have more distance from those years and am comfortable in my secular humanism, will that part of the book still seem as insightful to me?</span>
  <a data-text-id="9605611712176433375" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


